dcterms:description: The Beijing cohort dataset comprises resting-state fMRI (rs-fMRI) data from 198 young adults, including 76 males and 122 females, all aged between 18 and 26 years. The fMRI data for each participant consisted of 33 slices captured over 225 timepoints.
dcterms:title: Beijing cohort dataset

dcterms:description: The 1000 Functional Connectomes Project is a large-scale initiative that provides a comprehensive database of resting-state fMRI data, facilitating the study of brain connectivity and functional networks.
